Cabinet has announced that it will seek leave to appeal the judgment of the High Court in Pretoria on lockdown regulations. On Tuesday, the court ruled that Alert Levels 3 and 4 lockdown regulations were unconstitutional and invalid in a case that lobby group AfriForum had brought. However, the court suspended the judgment for two weeks to allow the cabinet to amend and republish the lockdown regulations. Minister in the Presidency, Jackson Mthembu, is currently briefing the media “virtually” on the outcomes of the latest Cabinet meeting from Pretoria. Live stream:  South Africa has been under a COVID-19 National State of Disaster since the 15th of March this year and under lockdown since the 27th of March. On 1 June, the country moved to alert Level 3 since past Monday. Below is the Cabinet statement in full: 